description:
WebOS Quick Install (WOSQI) is a powerful cross-platform homebrew tool that can install apps, patches, and other packages. It also has a few more advanced features for longtime homebrew users.

WOSQI is the first step into the homebrew world for most people. In the past, information on how to setup and use it, has been difficulty to easily find.

This app solves the problem. The most detailed documentation for WOSQI, this guide is a must for every user wanting to get the most out of their device through homebrew.

Features:
- Detailed step-by-step directions
- Screenshots to make things simpler
- Advanced topics for experienced users
- Interactive problem troubleshooter

This app was written by the developer of WOSQI, Jason Robitaille (myself). Over the past 2 years, I've helped countless webOS users enter the homebrew community and contributed dozens of patches and apps. This guide is a way to help countless more and support the work I'm doing.

I full intend to release updates to this app, as the the homebrew standard (& WOSQI) continue to change and evolve. Currently, it only supports English, however, if would like to contribute a translation, contact me at support@canuckcoding.ca.
